          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/israel-strikes-sanaa-after-houthi-missile-launch.jpg" alt="The attack comes a day after the Houthi armed group fired two projectiles toward Israel that were shot down by Israeli air defense" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>
          The attack comes a day after the Houthi armed group fired two projectiles toward Israel that were shot down by Israeli air defenses. Credits: Mohammed HUWAIS / AFP</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        Israel announced <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-29-may-25-spotlights-h1-1-another-airstrike" target="_blank">another airstrike</a> on Sanaa International Airport. The attacks destroyed the runway and Yemenia Airways‚Äô last operational civilian aircraft. The plane was scheduled to take those performing the Muslim Hajj pilgrimage to Saudi Arabia. Israel targeted what it called ‚Äúterror targets‚Äù linked to the Houthis. This measure shows Israel's zero-tolerance policy for cross-border attacks.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
      The UN called on all stakeholders, including the Houthis, to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-29-may-25-spotlights-h1-2-de-escalate" target="_blank">de-escalate</a> and exercise restraint, uphold their obligations under international law, and protect civilian infrastructure. They also urged the warring parties to return to the intra-Yemeni dialogue, with the support of the region for lasting peace. </p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        The strikes were a direct response to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-29-may-25-spotlights-h1-3-houthi-missile-launches" target="_blank">Houthi missile launches</a> aimed at Israeli territory. Israel sees the Houthis as an extension of Iran, shifting focus away from Yemen‚Äôs internal issues. This amplifies the ongoing regional conflict stretching from Gaza to the Red Sea. </p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        Sanaa airport, the largest in Yemen, came back into service last week after temporary repairs and runway restoration following previous Israeli attacks.</p>
