          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">
        Shadow fleet crisis
       </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
         <strong>
         Summary: 20% of global tankers are anonymously owned, which raises marine safety concerns. </strong>
         </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        The emergence of a ‚Äúshadow fleet,‚Äù comprising approximately <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-29-may-25-analysis-h1-8-700-unregulated-oil-tankers" target="_blank">700 unregulated oil tankers</a>, highlights a maritime crisis stemming from Western sanctions on Iran and Russia. These old, anonymously owned vessels account for nearly one-fifth of the global tanker fleet. They covertly transport sanctioned oil, mainly to China, a major importer. Many of these ships lack proper flag registration. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        This situation harms maritime safety and raises the risk of environmental disasters. It also weakens the authority of the UN Convention on the Law of the Sea. Efforts by the UN and the International Maritime Organization to regulate this issue has been unsuccessful, primarily due to geopolitical divisions. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        Meanwhile, countries such as Indonesia, Singapore, and the UAE permit these ships to anchor in their waters without much challenge. Since March, nearly 40% of Iranian oil carriers have used fraudulent flags. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        Judicial ambiguity and weak enforcement enable illicit trade to flourish. It also delivers leverage in global diplomacy. Nations wanting favorable US trade deals could gain power by agreeing to crack down on unflagged vessels. 
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
